==== Uncommon archive format support ====
PeaZip has full support for various LPAQ and [[PAQ]] formats, QUAD and BALZ (highly efficient [[ROLZ]] based compressors), [[FreeArc]] format, and for its native [[List of archive formats|PEA]] format.

7-Zip includes read support for [[.msi]], [[cpio]] and [[xar (archiver)|xar]], plus Apple's [[Apple Disk Image|dmg]]/[[Hierarchical File System|HFS]] disk images and the [[deb (file format)|deb]]/[[RPM Package Manager|.rpm]] package distribution formats; beta versions (9.07 onwards) have full support for the LZMA2-compressed .[[xz]] format.<ref name="7zipHistory">{{cite web | url =http://www.7-zip.org/history.txt | title =HISTORY of the 7-Zip | publisher =www.7-zip.org | date =2010-04-15 | accessdate =2010-04-24 }}</ref>

