{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}} {{Infobox book series | name = Köksalmanack | image = | image_caption = | books = | author = | editors = | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Sweden]] | language = [[Swedish language|Swedish]] | genre = [[almanac]]-[[cookbook]] | discipline = | publisher = | pub_date = 1933– | english_pub_date = | media_type = | number_of_books = | list_books = | preceded by = | followed by = }} '''Köksalmanack''' is a [[Sweden|Swedish]] combined [[almanac]]-[[cookbook]]. Since 1933 it has been published every year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hd.se/kultur/boken/2004/12/23/i-koeket-staar-tiden-stilla/|title=I köket står tiden stilla|publisher=Helsingborgs Dagblad|language=Swedish|author=Jörgen Andersson|date=23 December 2004|accessdate=19 December 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019184416/http://hd.se/kultur/boken/2004/12/23/i-koeket-staar-tiden-stilla/|archivedate=19 October 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
The earlier title, '''Husmoderns köksalmanack''', was dropped in 1979.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsd.se/kultur/artikel.aspx?ArticleId=7257464|title=Gisslan mellan thailandrecept och grilltrenden|publisher=Norrländska socialdemokraten|language=Swedish|author=Maria Vedin|date=5 November 2012|accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>
